body_text.text:
To evaluate the putative functional polymorphisms, we assessed actual promoter activity with the luciferase reporter assay (Fig. 3
). We prepared two reporter constructs that contained the A or G allele of the human IFITM1 gene g.-1920G>A polymorphisms. In the SW480 cells, the luciferase activity in the cells with the A allele in the IFITM1 g.-1920G>A polymorphism was significantly higher than that in the cells with the G allele (P
 = 0.05). This result suggests that the g.-1920A allele might affect the increased transcriptional activity of the IFITM1 gene in vivo.
